  "_doc": "Phase-6 demo: hierarchical export. The scene has TWO instances of a 2:1 mux sub-circuit feeding their outputs into an XOR gate. Click VERILOG to see:\n  • A separate `module mux2(...)` definition emitted ABOVE the top, with its own internal `and`/`or`/`not` primitives — the inner scene's body lifted into a real Verilog hierarchy instead of being inlined twice.\n  • Content-hash de-duplication — only ONE `module mux2(...)` definition for both instances. Top instantiates it twice with named ports: `mux2 mx_lo (.a(in_a), ...)` and `mux2 mx_hi (.a(in_c), ...)`.\n  • Definition order — sub-modules first, top last (Verilog needs definitions before use). The exporter walks the registry in encounter order, with nested sub-circuits already de-duped.\n  • Switch tabs in the modal: `top.v` → see the wiring; `top_tb.v` → see how the auto-TB just feeds the four primary inputs (it doesn't know about the inner ports). Right-click any block → `Copy as Verilog` to grab a snippet for that block alone.",
